Add scheduled commands.

Adds a view for listing and creating scheduled commands, which are 
commands that run at a specified interval automatically. A management
command processes all scheduled commands and executes any commands that
are due to run; this command should be run by a cronjob at the lowest
interval rate (15 minutes).

Split up project details into multiple pages.

This makes the project views a bit less muddled in what they do, and
gives us room to add another tab for managing the command schedule.

Add version field to command JSON.

This will help us identify which version of the communication between
captain and shove a specific order or event is tied to.
Add display names for users and a form for editing them.

Add capability to log the output of commands executed by shove.

Captain now sends two extra pieces of info to shove: a log_key, which
identifies the log that the command's output should be written to, and
a logging_queue, which identifies the queue on which captain will listen
for logging events.

When shove finishes executing a command, it will send a message over the
queue that captain specified containing the output of the executed 
command. Captain, listening via a management command 
`monitor_log_events`, receives the message and writes it to a file in
the media directory.
